{"blocks":[{"key":"6reb1","text":"Quickly remove the brain from the skull while the head is kept submerged in the ice-cooled cutting solution and isolate the cerebellum under the stereomicroscope.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"72tus","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"9a7iq","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"8eq2t","text":"During the production of slices, all procedures must be carried out in an ice-cold cutting solution.","type":"unstyled"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"length":1,"offset":138}],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"aipej","text":"To keep the temperature a few degrees above °C during the dissection, prepare some blocks of frozen cutting solution to be added to the      chilled solution contained in the Petri dish used to dissect the brain.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{"0":{"data":{"error_temperature":false,"guid":"BD455ADCDFFD11EC8C430A58A9FEAC02","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"temperature":"4","unit":10},"mutability":"MUTABLE","type":"temperature"}}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dd4hs","text":"Before cutting, completely remove the meninges with a pair of N.7 Dupont forceps. Place the cerebellum on the stage of the tissue chopper within a drop of the ice-cooled cutting solution. Operate the chopper and cut 350 μm-thick parasagittal slices. Once terminated slicing, collect slices with a curved spatula (they are usually stuck together) and place them in a sterile 50-mm Petri filled with the ice-cooled solution. Store at  until ready to separate slices. Separate individual slices under the stereomicroscope with a spatula and a needle, trying not to damage the tissue. During the entire procedure, slices must be submerged in the ice-cooled cutting solution. Discharge damaged slices. {"blocks":[{"key":"56nk9","text":"Collect slices one by one and carefully lift them onto the dry Millicell membrane. Once the required number of slices has been plated in the insert, place it inside a 35-mm Petri dish containing the required amount of medium. Be careful to avoid air bubbles forming between the insert membrane and the medium, i.e. check that the membrane's lower surface is completely wet.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
